**Previous answer:**

I don&#39;t believe there is currently a way for this particular setting. Normally emulator setting are saved into `AVD.conf`. [Here](https://android.googlesource.com/platform/external/qemu/+/6d16a2cfb5356046e813672b99ef54431eaf1748/android/android-emu/android/skin/qt/qt-settings.h) are all the constants for the persistent settings and microphone settings are not among them. Looking further at the `Virtual microphone uses host audio input` setting I found [the commit](https://android.googlesource.com/platform/external/qemu/+/e11e36e2d89059f72bb0eda6979ff57588f939a8) which introduced this setting and as you can see when you toggle this setting it sets `allow_real_audio` in audio subsystem and that&#39;s it. No other code is setting this flag. As you can see [here](https://developer.android.com/studio/releases/emulator#disable-host-audio) this option is being reset on restart intentionally and hopefully it will be fixed when the described bug is fixed.

Edit: here is a bit more on how exactly the flag is set:
UI switch toggle is handled in [this line](https://android.googlesource.com/platform/external/qemu/+/e11e36e2d89059f72bb0eda6979ff57588f939a8/android/android-emu/android/skin/qt/extended-pages/microphone-page.cpp#77). It calls [this function](https://android.googlesource.com/platform/external/qemu/+/e11e36e2d89059f72bb0eda6979ff57588f939a8/android-qemu2-glue/qemu-vm-operations-impl.cpp), which in its turn calls [qemu_allow_real_audio](https://android.googlesource.com/platform/external/qemu/+/e11e36e2d89059f72bb0eda6979ff57588f939a8/audio/audio.c#1208), which sets `allow_real_audio` flag. This flag is used in the `AUD_read` function
